  "prompt": "What are some locations in Tennessee that are suitable for a prom?",
  "response": "Tennessee offers a variety of beautiful venues suitable for prom events. Here are some locations that are popular for hosting proms:\n\n1. **The Factory at Franklin (Franklin)** - A unique historic venue with multiple event spaces that can accommodate large groups.\n\n2. **Chattanooga Choo Choo (Chattanooga)** - This historic train station and hotel features several event spaces, including a beautiful ballroom.\n\n3. **The Bell Tower (Nashville)** - Located in downtown Nashville, this venue features stunning architecture and elegant spaces perfect for a prom.\n\n4. **The Event Center at the Nashville Fairgrounds (Nashville)** - A versatile space that can accommodate large crowds, with modern amenities.\n\n5. **The War Memorial Auditorium (Nashville)** - This historic venue has a grand setting and a rich history, making it a unique choice for prom.\n\n6. **The Cotton Museum (Memphis)** - A unique venue with a blend of history and modern ambiance, perfect for a memorable prom night.\n\n7. **Memphis Botanic Garden (Memphis)** - Featuring beautiful gardens and event spaces, this venue offers a scenic backdrop for prom.\n\n8. **The Knoxville Museum of Art (Knoxville)** - A modern venue that provides a creative and artistic environment, ideal for a stylish prom.\n\n9. **The Music City Center (Nashville)** - A large convention center with various rooms and spaces, capable of accommodating a big prom event.\n\n10. **Hutton Hotel (Nashville)** - A modern boutique hotel with elegant spaces perfect for a more sophisticated prom event.\n\nWhen choosing a venue, consider the size of your prom, the theme, and the amenities you want available (such as catering, decor, and audiovisual equipment). It's also a good idea to book well in advance to secure your preferred location.",
